# Docs (internal, not deployed)
docs/*
!docs/handoffs/
!backend/docs/
# Positioning-map design-handoff artifacts describe a live site-wide trust
# asset; keep them tracked so documentation stays reconcilable with the live
# /positioning-map surface for future authoring sessions. Three-rule sequence
# is required because git can't re-include a file whose parent directory is
# already excluded by `docs/*` — we un-ignore the positioning dir, re-ignore
# its direct children (e.g., matrix exports, zips), then un-ignore the one
# design-handoff subdir we want tracked.
!docs/positioning/
docs/positioning/*
!docs/positioning/design_handoff_positioning_map/

